      • ACTION_SELECT_DUPLICATE_OVERRIDE

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_SELECT_DUPLICATE_OVERRIDE
        Activity Action: Select Re-auth Option after getting DUP response
        "com.pax.us.pay.action.SELECT_DUPLICATE_OVERRIDE"
        This action is host dependent.

        Not apply for all BroadPOS apps. It depends on Host support. Example: Do a CREDIT SALE transaction using BroadPOS CardKnox, response from host tells it is duplicated. The BroadPOS CardKnox will start this action with option DuplicateType.OVERRIDE,
        If choose OVERRIDE, BroadPOS will do re-auth for this transaction. If decline the option by cancel, BroadPOS will treat this transaction as declined.

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_PACKAGE - is the package name of caller.
        Type: String

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_TRANS_MODE - is transaction mode.
        Type: String
        See TransMode for details

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_TRANS_TYPE - is trans name.
        Type: String
        Example: "CREDIT SALE"

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_TIMEOUT -
        Type: Long
        Unit: ms
        Default is 30000.
        For reference only, BroadPOS handles timeout.

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_OPTIONS -
        Type: String[]
        See DuplicateType

        Output: EntryRequest.PARAM_INDEX - Selected Index
        Type: Integer
        Value start from 0.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
